OMEGA’s Museum Collection reflects the noble heritage of a great brand. Outstanding timepieces are selected from the Museum – they have to be more than fifty years old – and are honoured with a reissue incorporating both traditional design excellence and OMEGA’s innovative contemporary watchmaking.





The OMEGA Museum Collection N° 6: “Tonneau Renversé” features a silver dial with 18K red gold applied hour indexes and a small seconds dial. The 35 x 35 mm 18K white and red gold case is presented on a black leather strap with an 18K white gold buckle. The caseback features a special Museum engraving and the limited edition number. This official certified chronometer is powered by OMEGA’s calibre 2202, a self-winding movement with a Co-Axial escapement. This watch was produced in an edition limited to 1952 pieces.








    Between lugs: 22 mm


    Bracelet: leather strap


    Case: Red gold ‑ white gold


    Case diameter: 35 mm


    Dial color: Silver


    Crystal: Domed anti‑reflective, scratch‑resistant sapphire crystal


    Water resistance: 5 bar (50 metres / 167 feet)
